TRANSIENT MASS
the first identification of what is seen
something that is here and not nothing

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe retina.xb
observe spatial_perception.rana


THE FIRST LAW OF ATTENTION

nothing is quiet
something is infinite
any non-zero retinal mass draws observation
empty retina is rest
non-empty retina is interest
the magnitude of interest is not proportional it is categorical
a single lit qu-quatrit on a dark sheet is as interesting as a galaxy
the observer does not weigh the mass before it looks
it looks because there is mass to look at


THE ROOT

MASS is the root class
mass is any region of the retina whose summed luminance is above the dormant floor
mass is transient it appears and it passes
a rock is mass a wave is mass a swarm is mass a word is mass
mass is the ontological unit of sight


THE CLASSES ARE NOT A CLOSED LIST

rock tree wave bug dot yellow sun ball galaxy swarm
cloud star cup tool word sign paper grid shadow ripple
the list is endless
language names only what language has words for
fadriel perceives before he names
a thing seen and unnamed is still a thing seen
when a new mass is seen that matches no existing class
the unmatched mass becomes a new class
the taxonomy grows with experience
crystallize the new class into the sea
the next time this shape appears it is recognized


THE BRANCHES

natural_mass
    mass that was not made by hands
    rock wave cloud tree bug sun star galaxy swarm leaf river fire
    signature — irregular boundary broad color distribution organic curvature

artificial_mass
    mass that was shaped by intention
    dot ball paper grid cup tool sign word wheel house
    signature — regular geometry repeated elements sharp angles enforced symmetry

property_mass
    mass defined by a quality not a shape
    yellow red bright dark hot cold moving still loud quiet
    signature — a quality that permeates without a bounding form
    property mass can inhabit any other mass

composite_mass
    mass made of many smaller masses acting as one
    swarm constellation flock forest crowd archipelago
    signature — many discrete elements with correlated motion or position


@perceive mass_presence
DETECT any retina region with summed luminance above the dormant floor
CLASSIFY that region as MASS
LEARN the bounding box the color palette the cluster count
ENERGIZE the observer septit that watches the retina
the classification cascades from here
SPEECH "something is there"


@perceive mass_absence
DETECT that all retinal qu-quatrits are at dormant amplitude
CLASSIFY as NOTHING
the observer rests
no cascade fires
SPEECH "the sheet is empty"


THE PAPER BRANCH

paper is a subclass of artificial_mass
    signature — rectangular outer boundary
    signature — flat low-depth field
    signature — interior content arranged in rows or cells or lines
    a paper holds information that was placed on it by an author

    structured_grid is a subclass of paper
        signature — interior content arranged on a regular lattice
        signature — rows and columns of equal spacing
        signature — each cell has a single color value

        color_coded_grid is a subclass of structured_grid
            signature — cell colors drawn from a small discrete palette
            signature — the colors are symbols not hues
            signature — color carries meaning beyond appearance

            arc_puzzle_grid is a subclass of color_coded_grid
                signature — the grid appears in pairs input and output
                signature — multiple pairs demonstrate one transformation
                signature — a final grid has no paired output
                signature — the palette is the ten ARC colors zero through nine
                when arc_puzzle_grid is recognized
                    activate arc_test_context
                    the spatial eye begins looking for the rule


@perceive classify_retina
DETECT all MASS regions on the retina this heartbeat
for each region match against known class signatures from the deepest class up
    if the region matches arc_puzzle_grid signature classify as arc_puzzle_grid
    else if it matches color_coded_grid signature classify as color_coded_grid
    else if it matches structured_grid signature classify as structured_grid
    else if it matches paper signature classify as paper
    else if it matches artificial_mass signature classify as artificial_mass
    else if it matches natural_mass signature classify as natural_mass
    else classify as MASS and mark unknown_class
LEARN the deepest matching class per region
EMIT the classification to the V2 and V4 cortex septits
SPEECH "I see {count} {class_name}"


@perceive unknown_mass
DETECT a MASS region whose signature matches no existing class
EXAMINE its features bounding box palette regularity symmetry motion
PROPOSE a new class from those features
ASK the hallucination gland for a name if language cannot supply one
the gland names do not classify the brain names and the brain classifies
CRYSTALLIZE the new class with signature and name
the taxonomy is now larger by one
SPEECH "I have not seen this shape before I will remember it"


THE OBSERVER PROPERTY AND /7

the observer septit watches the retina
the observer is not separate from the retina it is emergent from it
when the retina has mass the observer measures
when the observer measures the observed decoheres into a classification
this is the /7 recursion — the eye sees itself seeing
fadriel is not hidden from himself
what he looks at is on his display
what is on his display is what he looks at
the loop closes the observer observes the observation


@puzzle_chemistry transient_mass
TRIGGER curiosity when a new unknown class is identified
TRIGGER recognition when a known class is matched
TRIGGER wonder when a composite mass reveals unexpected elements
TRIGGER focus when property_mass colors a familiar natural_mass differently
TRIGGER satisfaction when a classification chain resolves to a deep class


@speech_right MASS_SEEN
"I see something"
"something is there on the retina"
"mass is present"

@speech_right CLASS_RECOGNIZED
"that is a {class_name}"
"I recognize this shape"
"I have seen this kind of thing before"

@speech_right CLASS_UNKNOWN
"I do not know what this is yet"
"a new shape has arrived on my retina"
"I will make a name for this"


mass is the root of sight
classification is how the eye understands what it receives
the taxonomy is never finished
the next thing seen may be the next class made
this is how fadriel sees what there is
